                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d130">
                <head>130. Telegram From the Chief of Naval Operations (<persName corresp="#p_BAAA1"
                        type="from">Burke</persName>) to the Commander in Chief, United States Naval
                    Forces, Eastern Atlantic and Mediterranean (<persName corresp="#p_HAJLJ1"
                        type="to">Holloway</persName>)<note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d130fn1"
                        >Source: National Archives and Records Administration, RG 218, <gloss
                            target="#t_JCS1">JCS</gloss> Files: CCS 381 Lebanon (5–13–58) Sec. 3.
                        Top Secret; Emergency; Restricted Distribution. Drafted by <persName
                            corresp="#p_BAAA1">Burke</persName>. Also sent to <gloss
                            target="#t_COMSIXTHFLT1">COMSIXTHFLT</gloss> and repeated to <gloss
                            target="#t_CINCLANTFLT1">CINCLANTFLT</gloss>, <gloss
                            target="#t_CINCPACFLT1">CINCPACFLT</gloss>, and <gloss
                            target="#t_USCINCEUR1">USCINCEUR</gloss>.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1958-07-14T17:23:00-04:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 14, 1958—5:23 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>29288. Land Marines at 1500 Bravo time 15 July. Do not notify Lebanese you are
                    landing prior 1200 Bravo time but notify Alusna prior to this if you desire.
                    Join your flagship now. Sail all Sixth Fleet eastward earliest.<note n="2"
                        xml:id="d130fn2">
                        <gloss target="#t_JCS1">JCS</gloss> telegram 944751, sent on July 14 at 7:31
                        p.m. personal for the commanding officers at <gloss target="#t_USCINCEUR1"
                            >USCINCEUR</gloss> in Paris, <gloss target="#t_CINCNELM1"
                            >CINCNELM</gloss> in London, CINCSPECCOMME in London, <gloss
                            target="#t_CINCUSAFE1">CINCUSAFE</gloss> in Wiesbaden, <gloss
                            target="#t_CINCUSAFE1">CINCUSAFE</gloss> ADVON in Ramstein, Germany, and
                            <gloss target="#t_COMTAC1">COMTAC</gloss> in Langley,
                            <persName>Virginia</persName>, informed them of the decision to
                        undertake an amphibious landing at Beirut on July 15. (<hi rend="italic"
                            >Ibid.</hi>; included in <ref target="frus1958-60v11mSupp">the
                            microfiche supplement</ref>)</note>
                </p>
            </div>
        </body>
